reviewText: I have all of John Browns DVDs, this DVD was a great source of information for head casting but I would suggest getting volume 5 first.

I have the whole series, and this is one of the better ones. They are all very good, but molding always gives me the heebie-geebies, I just know I'll bump something. So, its nice to watch the dvd to get a refresher class, before tackling my own project.

My only complaint is that the narrative seems like an after-thought.
